<Author>belaso
<Content>I changed after first night I had a whole reservation in this hotel, but only stayed the first one, then I went to another one. My company made the reservation for me, and thought, according to its name Ritz that it would be a nice hotel. It's absolutly not nice.Lobby, restaurant, bar and reception are all together in the same small room in the first floor (ground floor only for the lift and and stairs).Rooms are quite big, but furniture, carpet, bathroom and everything is so old... They have tried to renew the bathroom painting the sanitaries with white matt paint!! It looks dirty and unsafe. There is not air conditiones, but they supplie it with a fan. It's so hot that you can hardly sleep. And if you want to open the window you have to suffer the noise of all the air conditioner's motors of the buildings around.I cant say nothing about breakfast, it was not included and I went somewhere else.Well, as you can imagine I will never go to this hotel again.I have to say that it was very cheap, 30 euros/night, and that it is well situated in the historical center, but it's not worth it.I changed to Meli谩 Mexico Reforma for the following 6 nights, which has nothig to do with this, of course. 
